# Local Claude Instructions — [DEVICE NAME]

## Paths (fill in per device)
- brain-kit repo: [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT]        # e.g. ~/brain-kit
- Claude config dir: [PATH_TO_CLAUDE_DIR]    # e.g. ~/.claude

## brain-kit sync

brain-kit is the source of truth for all skills, agents, prompts, and configs.
Local copies in ~/.claude are disposable — always sync from the repo, not the other way around
unless you are explicitly pushing an improvement back.

### Pulling from brain-kit → ~/.claude

To deploy a skill locally:
```
cp -r [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT]/skills/<skill-name> [PATH_TO_CLAUDE_DIR]/skills/
```

To deploy all skills at once:
```
cp -r [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT]/skills/. [PATH_TO_CLAUDE_DIR]/skills/
```

To deploy a config:
```
cp [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT]/configs/<file> [PATH_TO_CLAUDE_DIR]/
```

### Pushing improvements back to brain-kit

If a skill or asset was edited locally and should be persisted:
1. Copy the edited file back to the repo: `cp [PATH_TO_CLAUDE_DIR]/skills/<skill>/<file> [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT]/skills/<skill>/`
2. cd into brain-kit, review the diff, commit, and push.
3. Never commit device-specific files (this claude.md) — it is gitignored.

### Pulling latest from remote

```
cd [PATH_TO_BRAIN_KIT] && git pull
```

Run this on each device to stay in sync after pushing from another machine.

## What lives where

| Asset | Source of truth | Local copy location |
|---|---|---|
| Skills | brain-kit/skills/ | ~/.claude/skills/ |
| Agents | brain-kit/agents/ | ~/.claude/agents/ |
| Prompts | brain-kit/prompts/ | ~/.claude/ or project dirs |
| Configs | brain-kit/configs/ | ~/.claude/ |
| This file | NOT committed (gitignored) | ~/.claude/claude.md or ~/brain-kit/claude.md |
